We went to try this Mexican restaurant, and we can start by saying: 100% recommended.
We only knew the nachos from this cuisine, so we let the owner, Emilio, advise us‚Ä¶ and it was a wonderful gastronomic experience.

Nachos, tacos, quesadillas‚Ä¶ everything was delicious. You can taste the quality of the ingredients and how they differentiate each dish: tacos, fajitas, quesadillas‚Ä¶ nothing tasted the same. The spiciness was just right: lively but not over the top.

Afterwards, Emilio suggested a tequila liqueur with chocolate to whet our appetite for the signature dessert: sweet corn bread with dulce de leche and a pink salt that contrasts beautifully.
